         <div type="edition" xml:lang="ocm-Latn" rendition="class:83233 maturity:00000">
           <ab><milestone type="pagelike" unit="face" n="A"/><lb n="A01"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="11" unit="character"/><seg type="aksara"><seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>u</seg> <gap reason="lost" quantity="12" unit="character"/>
           <!--sapi2argr On the rtf and txt, this lign is counted 0, so I encoded it "A01". -->
         </ab>
         <p><lb n="A1"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> mvaun· paliy· <seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>v<seg type="component" subtype="vowel"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg> <gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A2"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/> luvu subhāḥ di kadyaṅ· <gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A3"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/> humā tavauṅ· di luvu lamauṅ· li<unclear>m</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ā</supplied> <gap reason="lost" quantity="7" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A4"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/> Asiy·<g type="dotMid">.</g> dandau tavauṅ· lagaiḥ Aviḥ<g type="dotMid">.</g> humā luvu klā d<gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A5"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> jāk· Asīy·<g type="dotMid">.</g> humā vasauṅ· pāk· pluḥ tijuḥ galauk·<g type="dotMid">.</g> dvā pluḥ tiju<unclear>ḥ</unclear> <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A6"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/>ṅ· lagaiḥ Aviḥ<g type="dotMid">.</g> humā di kalataiḥ<g type="dotMid">.</g> humā klov·
         karuñak·<!-- sapi2argr comment of the rtf:  karuñak: this reading is very likely wrong. I have seen somewhere else the letter here rendered as ña, but do not remember where nor what the correct interpretation is. --> pāk· galauk·<g type="dandaPlain">.</g> tluv· jāk<supplied reason="lost">·</supplied> <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="A7"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> humā di Andap· mvaun· paliy· kalataiḥ pāk· galauk·<g type="dotMid">.</g> dvā jāk· <unclear>A</unclear>siy· <g type="ddandaHooked"/><g type="floretComplex"/>
         <lb n="A8"/>humā manrauṅ· yām̃ tandyo tuy· thauṅ·<!-- sapi2argr thauṅ·: or read dhauṅ·, mauṅ·? --> nan· la<unclear>gai</unclear>ḥ Aviḥ
         </p>
         <p><milestone type="pagelike" unit="face" n="B"/>
         <lb n="B1"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
         <lb n="B2"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="9" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">h</supplied>u<unclear>m</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ā</supplied> <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> yā <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/>
         <lb n="B3"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" unit="character"/> <unclear>glai</unclear> da<seg type="aksara"><seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>i</seg> <seg type="aksara"><seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>va</seg>ra Akā<unclear>ra</unclear> dana<!-- sapi2argr tanadaḥ: Akā(ra) dana. I read an initial A followed by a ka with a long central vertical trait--> glai n<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">i</supplied><unclear>y·</unclear><!-- sapi2argr n(V/·): n[i](y·). This reading is highly conjectural. Maybe read nV{1}. -->
         <lb n="B4"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="8" unit="line"/><unclear>ḥ</unclear> Aviḥ hu
         </p>
